longBusinessSummary: Liechtensteinische Landesbank Aktiengesellschaft provides banking products and services in Liechtenstein, Switzerland, Germany, Austria, and internationally. It operates through Retail & Corporate Banking, and International Wealth Management. The company offers savings, payment, current, rent, rental deposit savings, and business investment accounts. It also provides safe deposit box and securities safe custody, debit and credit cards, and digital solutions; and investment advice, asset management, funds, structured products, derivative transactions, securities lending, borrowing, and pension schemes. In addition, the company offers direct investment products comprising money market, equities, bonds, medium-term notes, time deposits, foreign exchange transactions and precious metals; mortgages, business, investment, Lombard loans, as well as advances; real estate financing; and guarantees and sureties. Further, it provides payment, interbank, online and mobile banking, and securities trading services. The company operates through branches in Liechtenstein, Austria, Switzerland, Dubai, Zurich, Geneva, and Abu Dhabi. Liechtensteinische Landesbank Aktiengesellschaft was founded in 1861 and is headquartered in Vaduz, Liechtenstein.
